<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Judges 5:1-31</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="21">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="31">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And on that day Deb&acute;o&middot;rah along with Ba&acute;rak the son of A&middot;bin&acute;o&middot;am broke out in song, saying:</span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">“For letting the hair hang loose in Israel [for war],<br><span class="z">For the people’s volunteering,</span><br><span class="z">B<span class="smallcaps">LESS</span> Jehovah.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Listen, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> kings; give ear, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> high officials:<br><span class="z">I to Jehovah, yes, I, will sing.</span><br><span class="z">I shall make melody to Jehovah, Israel’s God.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Jehovah, at your going forth from Se&acute;ir,<br><span class="z">At your marching out of the field of E&acute;dom,</span><br><span class="p">Earth rocked, heavens also dripped,</span><br><span class="z">Clouds also dripped with water.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Mountains flowed away from the face of Jehovah,<br><span class="z">This Si&acute;nai away from the face of Jehovah, Israel’s God.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">In the days of Sham&acute;gar the son of A&acute;nath,<br><span class="z">In the days of Ja&acute;el, pathways had no traffic,</span><br><span class="z">And the travelers of roadways would travel by roundabout pathways.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">The dwellers in open country ceased, in Israel they ceased,<br><span class="z">Until I, Deb&acute;o&middot;rah, rose up,</span><br><span class="z">Until I rose up as a mother in Israel.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">They proceeded to choose new gods.<br><span class="z">It was then there was war in the gates.</span><br><span class="p">A shield could not be seen, nor a lance,</span><br><span class="z">Among forty thousand in Israel.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">My heart is for the commanders of Israel,<br><span class="z">Who were volunteers among the people.</span><br><span class="z">B<span class="smallcaps">LESS</span> Jehovah.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> riders on yellowish-red she-asses,<br><span class="z">Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> who sit on rich carpets,</span><br><span class="p">And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> who walk on the road,</span><br><span class="z">Consider!</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Some of the voices of the water distributors among the places of drawing water,<br><span class="z">There they began to recount the righteous acts of Jehovah,</span><br><span class="p">The righteous acts of his dwellers in open country in Israel.</span><br><span class="z">It was then Jehovah’s people made their way down to the gates.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Awake, awake, O Deb&acute;o&middot;rah;<br><span class="z">Awake, awake, utter a song!</span><br><span class="z">Rise up, Ba&acute;rak, and lead your captives away, you son of A&middot;bin&acute;o&middot;am!</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">It was then the survivors came down to the majestic ones;<br><span class="z">Jehovah’s people came down to me against the mighty ones.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Out of E&acute;phra&middot;im was their origin in the low plain,<br><span class="z">With you, O Benjamin, among your peoples.</span><br><span class="p">Out of Ma&acute;chir the commanders went down,</span><br><span class="z">And out of Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun those handling the equipment of a scribe.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And the princes in Is&acute;sa&middot;char were with Deb&acute;o&middot;rah,<br><span class="z">And as Is&acute;sa&middot;char, so was Ba&acute;rak.</span><br><span class="p">Into the low plain he was sent on foot.</span><br><span class="z">Among the divisions of Reu&acute;ben great were the searchings of the heart.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Why did you sit down between the two saddlebags,<br><span class="z">To listen to the pipings for the flocks?</span><br><span class="z">For the divisions of Reu&acute;ben there were great searchings of the heart.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Gil&acute;e&middot;ad kept to his residence on the other side of the Jordan;<br><span class="z">And Dan, why did he continue to dwell for the time in ships?</span><br><span class="p">Ash&acute;er sat idle at the seashore,</span><br><span class="z">And by his landing places he kept residing.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun was a people that scorned their souls to the point of death;<br><span class="z">Naph&acute;ta&middot;li also, on the heights of the field.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Kings came, they fought;<br><span class="z">It was then that the kings of Ca&acute;naan fought</span><br><span class="p">In Ta&acute;a&middot;nach by the waters of Me&middot;gid&acute;do.</span><br><span class="z">No gain of silver did they take.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">From heaven did the stars fight,<br><span class="z">From their orbits they fought against Sis&acute;e&middot;ra.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">The torrent of Ki&acute;shon washed them away,<br><span class="z">The torrent of ancient days, the torrent of Ki&acute;shon.</span><br><span class="z">You went treading down strength, O my soul.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">It was then that the hoofs of horses pawed<br><span class="z">Because of dashings upon dashings of his stallions.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">‘C<span class="smallcaps">URSE</span> Me&acute;roz,’ said the angel of Jehovah,<br><span class="z">‘C<span class="smallcaps">URSE</span> its inhabitants incessantly,</span><br><span class="p">For they did not come to the assistance of Jehovah,</span><br><span class="z">To the assistance of Jehovah with the mighty ones.’</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">Ja&acute;el the wife of He&acute;ber the Ken&acute;ite will be most blessed among women,<br><span class="z">Among women in the tent she will be most blessed.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">Water he asked, milk she gave;<br><span class="z">In the large banquet bowl of majestic ones she presented curdled milk.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Her hand to the tent pin she then thrust out,<br><span class="z">And her right hand to the mallet of hard workers.</span><br><span class="p">And she hammered Sis&acute;e&middot;ra, she pierced his head through,</span><br><span class="z">And she broke apart and cut up his temples.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">Between her feet he collapsed, he fell, he lay down;<br><span class="z">Between her feet he collapsed, he fell;</span><br><span class="z">Where he collapsed, there he fell overcome.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">From the window a woman looked out and kept watching for him,<br><span class="z">The mother of Sis&acute;e&middot;ra from the lattice,</span><br><span class="p">‘Why has his war chariot delayed in coming?</span><br><span class="z">Why must the hoofbeats of his chariots be so late?’</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">The wise ones of her noble ladies would answer her,<br><span class="z">Yes, she too would talk back to herself with her own sayings,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">‘Ought they not to find, ought they not to distribute spoil,<br><span class="z">A womb—two wombs to every able-bodied man,</span><br><span class="z">Spoil of dyed stuffs for Sis&acute;e&middot;ra, spoil of dyed stuffs,</span><br><span class="p">An embroidered garment, dyed stuff, two embroidered garments</span><br><span class="z">For the necks of [men of] spoil?’</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">Thus let all your enemies perish, O Jehovah,<br><span class="z">And let your lovers be as when the sun goes forth in its mightiness.”</span></span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs31-3">And the land had no further disturbance for forty years.</span>
</p>
</form>

