<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Judges 9:1-57</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="21">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="57">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">In time A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech the son of Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al went to She&acute;chem to the brothers of his mother and began speaking to them and to all the family of the house of his mother’s father, saying:</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">“Speak, please, in the hearing of all the landowners of She&acute;chem, ‘Which is better for <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>, for seventy men, all the sons of Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al, to rule over <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> or for one man to rule over <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>? And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must remember that <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> bone and <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> flesh I am.’”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">So the brothers of his mother began speaking all these words about him in the hearing of all the landowners of She&acute;chem so that their heart inclined toward A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech, for they said: “He is our own brother.”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Then they gave him seventy pieces of silver from the house of Ba&acute;al-be&acute;rith, and with them A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech proceeded to hire idle and insolent men, that they might accompany him.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">After that he went to the house of his father at Oph&acute;rah and killed his brothers, the sons of Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al, seventy men, upon one stone, but Jo&acute;tham the youngest son of Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al was left over, because he had hid.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Subsequently all the landowners of She&acute;chem and all the house of Mil&acute;lo gathered together and went and made A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech reign as king, close by the big tree, the pillar that was in She&acute;chem.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">When they reported it to Jo&acute;tham he at once went and stood on the top of Mount Ger&acute;i&middot;zim and raised his voice and called out and said to them: “Listen to me, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> landowners of She&acute;chem, and let God listen to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>:</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">“Once upon a time the trees went to anoint a king over them. So they said to the olive tree, ‘Do be king over us.’</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">But the olive tree said to them, ‘Must I give up my fatness with which they glorify God and men, and must I go to wave over the other trees?’</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Then the trees said to the fig tree, ‘You come, be queen over us.’</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">But the fig tree said to them, ‘Must I give up my sweetness and my good produce, and must I go to wave over the other trees?’</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Next the trees said to the vine, ‘You come, be queen over us.’</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">In turn the vine said to them, ‘Must I give up my new wine that makes God and men rejoice, and must I go to wave over the trees?’</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Finally all the other trees said to the bramble, ‘You come, be king over us.’</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">At this the bramble said to the trees, ‘If it is in truth that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are anointing me as king over <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>, come, seek refuge under my shadow. But if not, let fire come out of the bramble and consume the cedars of Leb&acute;a&middot;non.’</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">“And now if it is in truth and in faultlessness that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have acted and that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> went making A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech king, and if it is goodness that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have exercised toward Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al and his household, and if <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have done to him as the doing of his hands deserved,</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">when my father fought for <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> and went risking his soul that he might deliver <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> out of Mid&acute;i&middot;an’s hand;</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>, for <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> part, have risen up against the household of my father today that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> might kill his sons, seventy men, upon one stone, and that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> might make A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech, the son of his slave girl, king over the landowners of She&acute;chem just because he is <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> own brother;</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">yes, if it is in truth and in faultlessness that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have acted toward Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al and his household this day, rejoice over A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech and let him too rejoice over <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">But if not, let fire come out of A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech and consume the landowners of She&acute;chem and the house of Mil&acute;lo, and let fire come out of the landowners of She&acute;chem and the house of Mil&acute;lo and consume A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Then Jo&acute;tham took to flight and went running off and made his way to Be&acute;er, and he took up dwelling there because of A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech his brother.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech kept playing the prince over Israel three years.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Then God let develop a bad spirit between A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech and the landowners of She&acute;chem, and the landowners of She&acute;chem proceeded to deal treacherously with A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech,</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">that the violence done to the seventy sons of Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al might come and that he might put their blood upon A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech their brother because he killed them, and upon the landowners of She&acute;chem because they strengthened his hands to kill his brothers.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">So the landowners of She&acute;chem set ambush men for him upon the tops of the mountains, and they would rob everyone that would pass by them on the road. In time it was reported to A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Then Ga&acute;al the son of E&acute;bed and his brothers came and crossed over into She&acute;chem, and the landowners of She&acute;chem began to trust in him.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And they went out as usual into the field and engaged in gathering the grapes of their vineyards and in treading them and in carrying on a festal exultation, after which they went into the house of their god and ate and drank and called down evil upon A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And Ga&acute;al the son of E&acute;bed went on to say: “Who is A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech, and who is She&acute;chem that we should serve him? Is he not the son of Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al, and is not Ze&acute;bul a commissioner of his? Serve the men of Ha&acute;mor, She&acute;chem’s father, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> others, but why should we ourselves serve him?</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And if only this people were in my hand! Then I would remove A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech.” And he went on to say to A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech: “Make your army numerous and come on out.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">And Ze&acute;bul the prince of the city got to hear the words of Ga&acute;al the son of E&acute;bed. Then his anger blazed.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">So he sent messengers by subterfuge to A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech, saying: “Look! Ga&acute;al the son of E&acute;bed and his brothers are now come to She&acute;chem, and here they are massing the city against you.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And now rise up by night, you and the people that are with you, and lie in wait in the field.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And it must occur in the morning that as soon as the sun shines forth you should get up early, and you must make a dash against the city; and when he and the people that are with him are going out against you, you must also do to him just as your hand finds it possible.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">Accordingly A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech and all the people that were with him rose up by night, and they began to lie in wait against She&acute;chem in four bands.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">Later Ga&acute;al the son of E&acute;bed went out and stood at the entrance of the city gate. Then A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech and the people that were with him rose up from the place of ambush.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">When Ga&acute;al caught sight of the people, he at once said to Ze&acute;bul: “Look! People coming down from the tops of the mountains.” But Ze&acute;bul said to him: “The shadows of the mountains are what you are seeing as though they were men.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Later Ga&acute;al spoke once more and said: “Look! People coming down out of the center of the land, and one band is coming by the way of the big tree of Me&middot;on&acute;e&middot;nim.”</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">At this Ze&acute;bul said to him: “Where now is that saying of yours that you mouthed, ‘Who is A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech that we should serve him?’ Is not this the people whom you rejected? Go out now, please, and fight against them.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">So Ga&acute;al went on out at the head of the landowners of She&acute;chem and took up the fight against A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">And A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech set out after him, and he went fleeing before him; and the slain kept falling in numbers as far as the entrance of the gate.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">And A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech continued to dwell in A&middot;ru&acute;mah, and Ze&acute;bul proceeded to drive Ga&acute;al and his brothers out from dwelling in She&acute;chem.</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">And it came about on the next day that the people began to go out into the field. So they told A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech.</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">Hence he took the people and divided them up into three bands and began to lie in wait in the field. Then he looked, and there the people were going out of the city. He now rose up against them and struck them down.</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">And A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech and the bands that were with him made a dash that they might stand at the entrance of the city gate, while two bands made a dash against all who were in the field, and they went striking them down.</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">And A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech fought against the city all that day and got to capture the city; and he killed the people that were in it, after which he pulled the city down and sowed it with salt.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">When all the landowners of the tower of She&acute;chem heard of it, they immediately went to the vault of the house of El-be&acute;rith.</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">Then it was reported to A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech that all the landowners of the tower of She&acute;chem had collected together.</span> <a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">At that A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech went up Mount Zal&acute;mon, he and all the people that were with him. A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech now took an ax in his hand and cut down a branch of the trees and lifted it up and put it on his shoulder and said to the people that were with him: “What <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have seen me do—hurry up, do like me!”</span> <a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">So all the people cut down also each one a branch for himself and went following A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech. Then they put them against the vault, and over them they set the vault on fire, so that all the men of the tower of She&acute;chem died too, about a thousand men and women.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">And A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech proceeded to go to The&acute;bez and to camp against The&acute;bez and capture it.</span> <a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">As a strong tower happened to be in the middle of the city, there was where all the men and women and all the landowners of the city went fleeing, after which they shut it behind them and climbed onto the roof of the tower.</span> <a name="bk52" class="vsAnchor">52</a>
       <span id="vs52">And A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech made his way to the tower and began fighting against it, and he went on up close to the entrance of the tower to burn it with fire.</span> <a name="bk53" class="vsAnchor">53</a>
       <span id="vs53">Then a certain woman pitched an upper millstone upon A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech’s head and broke his skull in pieces.</span> <a name="bk54" class="vsAnchor">54</a>
       <span id="vs54">So he quickly called the attendant bearing his weapons and said to him: “Draw your sword and put me to death, for fear they should say about me, ‘It was a woman that killed him.’” Immediately his attendant ran him through, so that he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk55" class="vsAnchor">55</a>
       <span id="vs55">When the men of Israel got to see that A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech had died, they now went each one to his place.</span> <a name="bk56" class="vsAnchor">56</a>
       <span id="vs56">Thus God made the evil of A&middot;bim&acute;e&middot;lech that he had done to his father by killing his seventy brothers come back.</span> <a name="bk57" class="vsAnchor">57</a>
       <span id="vs57">And all the evil of the men of She&acute;chem God made come back upon their own heads, that the malediction of Jo&acute;tham the son of Jer&middot;ub&middot;ba&acute;al might come upon them.</span>
</p>
</form>

