<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Judges 18:1-31</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="21">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="31">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">In those days there was no king in Israel. And in those days the tribe of the Dan&acute;ites was looking for an inheritance for itself to dwell there; because up to that day an inheritance had not fallen to them in the midst of the tribes of Israel.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Eventually the sons of Dan sent five men of their family, men from among them, men who were valiant fellows, out from Zo&acute;rah and Esh&acute;ta&middot;ol, to spy out the land and to explore it. So they said to them: “Go, explore the land.” In time they came into the mountainous region of E&acute;phra&middot;im as far as the house of Mi&acute;cah and got to spend the night there.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">While they were close by the house of Mi&acute;cah, they recognized the voice of the young man, the Levite, so that they turned aside there. And they proceeded to say to him: “Who brought you here, and what are you doing in this place, and what interest do you have here?”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">In turn he said to them: “Thus and so Mi&acute;cah did for me that he might hire me, and that I might serve as priest for him.”</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Then they said to him: “Inquire, please, of God that we may know whether our way on which we are going will be successful.”</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So the priest said to them: “Go in peace. It is before Jehovah that <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> way is in which <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> go.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Accordingly the five men went on and came to La&acute;ish and saw how the people that were within it were dwelling in self-reliance according to the custom of the Si&middot;do&acute;ni&middot;ans, quiet and unsuspecting, and there was no oppressive conqueror that was molesting a thing in the land, while they were far off from the Si&middot;do&acute;ni&middot;ans and they had nothing to do with mankind.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">At length they came to their brothers at Zo&acute;rah and Esh&acute;ta&middot;ol, and their brothers began to say to them: “How was it with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>?”</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">At this they said: “Do get up, and let us go up against them; for we have seen the land, and, look! it is very good. And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are hesitant. Do not be sluggish about walking to come in to take possession of the land.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">When <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> come in, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will come to an unsuspecting people, and the land is quite wide; for God has given it into <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> hand, a place where there is no lack of any sort of thing that is in the earth.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Then six hundred men girded with weapons of war, out of the family of the Dan&acute;ites, departed from there, that is, from Zo&acute;rah and Esh&acute;ta&middot;ol.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And they got on their way up and went camping at Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim in Judah. That is why they have called that place Ma&acute;ha&middot;neh-dan down to this day. Look! It is west of Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">After that they passed along from there to the mountainous region of E&acute;phra&middot;im and came as far as the house of Mi&acute;cah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Then the five men that had gone to spy out the land of La&acute;ish answered and said to their brothers: “Did <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> know that there are in these houses an eph&acute;od and teraphim and a carved image and a molten statue? And now have in mind what <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> ought to do.”</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">So they turned aside there and came to the house of the young man, the Levite, at the house of Mi&acute;cah, and began to ask how he was getting along.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">All the while the six hundred men girded with their weapons of war, who were of the sons of Dan, were standing at the entrance of the gate.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">The five men that had gone to spy out the land now went on up, that they might enter in there to take the carved image and the eph&acute;od and the teraphim and the molten image. (And the priest was standing at the entrance of the gate with the six hundred men girded with weapons of war.)</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And these went into the house of Mi&acute;cah and proceeded to take the carved image, the eph&acute;od and the teraphim and the molten image. At that the priest said to them: “What are <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> doing?”</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">But they said to him: “Be quiet. Put your hand over your mouth, and go with us and become a father and a priest for us. Which is better, for you to continue a priest to the house of one man or for you to become a priest to a tribe and family in Israel?”</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">At this the heart of the priest was pleased, and he now took the eph&acute;od and the teraphim and the carved image and came into the midst of the people.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Then they turned and went their way and put the little ones and the livestock and the valuable things ahead of them.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">They themselves had got a distance away from the house of Mi&acute;cah when the men who were in the houses that were close by the house of Mi&acute;cah were called together and tried to catch up with the sons of Dan.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">When they kept crying out to the sons of Dan, then they turned their faces and said to Mi&acute;cah: “What is the matter with you that you have been called together?”</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">So he said: “My gods that I made <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have taken, the priest too, and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> go <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> way, and what do I have anymore? How, then, is it that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> can say to me, ‘What is the matter with you?’”</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">At this the sons of Dan said to him: “Do not let your voice be heard close to us, for fear that men bitter of soul may assault <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> people, and you have to forfeit your own soul and the soul of your household.”</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And the sons of Dan kept going on their way; and Mi&acute;cah got to see that they were stronger than he was, and so he turned and went back to his house.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">As for them, they took what Mi&acute;cah had made and the priest that had become his, and they kept going toward La&acute;ish, against a people quiet and unsuspecting. And they proceeded to strike them with the edge of the sword, and the city they burned with fire.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And there was no deliverer, for it was far away from Si&acute;don, and they had nothing at all to do with mankind; and it was in the low plain that belonged to Beth-re&acute;hob. Then they built the city and took up dwelling in it.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">Furthermore, they called the name of the city Dan by the name of their father, Dan, who had been born to Israel. Nevertheless, La&acute;ish was the city’s name at first.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">After that the sons of Dan stood up the carved image for themselves; and Jon&acute;a&middot;than the son of Ger&acute;shom, Moses’ son, he and his sons became priests to the tribe of the Dan&acute;ites until the day of the land’s being taken into exile.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And they kept the carved image of Mi&acute;cah, which he had made, set up for themselves all the days that the house of the [true] God continued in Shi&acute;loh.</span>
</p>
</form>

